# Indexable routes (mandatory)

When **matched files are in context**, any new or changed **indexable** page must ship crawler-visible HTML in `#root`, not title-only SPA shells.

**Source of truth:** `scripts/prerenderBodyRoutes.ts` — do not duplicate route lists elsewhere.

## Four-file checklist (every new indexable route)

1. **`src/App.tsx`** — client route
2. **`src/prerender/PrerenderApp.tsx`** — same route for build-time SSR markup
3. **`src/seo/pageSeoRegistry.ts`** — title, description, canonical, JSON-LD, sitemap
4. **`scripts/prerenderBodyRoutes.ts`** — add to `PRERENDER_BODY_EXACT` or ensure a matching `PRERENDER_BODY_PREFIXES` entry

**Gated / token URLs** (e.g. `/chatgpt-ads-cheat-sheet/guide`): add to `PRERENDER_BODY_EXCLUDE`, set `robots: noindex` in registry + `vercel.json` if applicable — head only, no body prerender.

## Build gate (non-negotiable)

- Agent runs **`npm run build`** before calling the page done — not a manual user step.
- Postbuild **`assertPrerenderBody`** fails if a prerender-body route ships empty `#root`.
- Do **not** hand-edit `public/sitemap.xml`, `llms-full.txt`, or `llm-context.json` (generated on build).

## Quick verify

```bash
npm run build
# H1 or key copy must appear inside dist/{route}/index.html #root
grep 'Your expected H1' dist/your-route/index.html
```

## Pair with other rules/skills

- **`stratezik-seo-master`** — schema, FAQs, blog `postsMeta` + `postLoaders`, release checklist
- **`stratezik-free-tool-design`** — lead-magnet landings under `src/components/` + `FREE_TOOLS[]`
- **`stratezik-web-performance`** — App shell lazy loading when touching `App.tsx`

## Anti-pattern

Registry + `PrerenderApp` without `prerenderBodyRoutes` → live page with `<title>` but empty `#root` (AI crawlers see a blank body). This happened on `/free-tools`; the build gate now prevents recurrence.
